  * gmond: use fabs[f] values for floating metrics absolute calculation
    Reference: http://sourceforge.net/mailarchive/forum.php?thread_name=20080421220317.GA1971%40golem.rich-paul.net&forum_name=ganglia-developers
    Patch: http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia/trunk/monitor-core/gmond/gmond.c?r1=1275&r2=1274&pathrev=1275
    +1: bnicholes
     0: 
    -1: 

  * gmetad: Don't overwrite the metric struct that is being built in 
     memory during the XML parsing with the summary metric structure.  
     Since multiple extra_data_element tags can exists for each metric, 
     the metric structure needs to be preserved until the last 
     extra_data_element tag is read. At the same time the summary metric 
     data needs to also be calculated and written to the hash table.  
     But they both can not use the same memory.
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia/trunk/monitor-core/gmetad/process_xml.c?r1=1238&r2=1301
    +1: bnicholes

